# Environment Variables Example
# 
# This file documents all environment variables used by the application.
# Copy this file and update with your actual values, or set them in your
# deployment platform's environment variable settings.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit actual values to version control!
# This file contains example/placeholder values only.

# ============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (Required)
# ============================================================================

# Supabase Project URL
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project URL
# Example: https://xxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Supabase Anonymous/Public Key
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project API keys → anon/public
# This is safe to expose in client-side code (it's public by design)
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ============================================================================
# SENTRY ERROR MONITORING (Optional)
# ============================================================================

# Sentry DSN for error tracking
# Get this from: Sentry Dashboard → Settings → Projects → Your Project → Client Keys (DSN)
# Leave empty or set to null to disable Sentry
# Example: https://xxxxx@xxxxx.ingest.sentry.io/xxxxx
SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn

# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT PLATFORM NOTES
# ============================================================================

# For Netlify:
# - Set these in: Site Settings → Environment Variables
# - Use build script to inject into public/env.js (see DEPLOYMENT.md)

# For Cloudflare Pages:
# - Set these in: Pages → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# - Use build script to inject into public/env.js (see DEPLOYMENT.md)

# For Vercel:
# - Set these in: Project Settings → Environment Variables
# - Use build script to inject into public/env.js (see DEPLOYMENT.md)

# For Manual Deployment:
# - Edit public/env.js directly with production values
# - Ensure window.__DEV__ is set to false for production

# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# ============================================================================

# Development mode is automatically detected based on hostname:
# - localhost, 127.0.0.1, 192.168.*, *.local → Development mode
# - All other hostnames → Production mode

# To force development mode in production (for testing only):
# Set window.__FORCE_DEBUG__ = true in browser console
# ⚠️ Never do this in actual production!

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================

# - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is safe to expose (it's public by design)
# - Never commit actual production keys to version control
# - Use environment variables in deployment platforms
# - Review public/env.js before each deployment
# - Ensure window.__DEV__ is false on production domains

